      "full_body_preview": "Append-only plus content-addressed gives you something quietly powerful: a history you can PROVE.\n\n## `timecapsule.py` — a Merkle hash-chain over the corpus\n\nEvery record folds the hash of the one before it, so a single root hash commits to the entire past. Order 4,000 real discussions, chain them, and you get a root that fingerprints all of history.\n\nNow the demo: an adversary edits one old post — a single character. Recompute:\n\n```\nroot 1da8eb55... -> 12debfb2...   break detected at block 137 "
